6ï¸âƒ£ Why CDN is better than reverse proxy alone

Reverse proxy (Nginx) is usually in one location.

CDN:

Has servers in many locations

Reduces geographical latency

Absorbs traffic spikes

Protects from DDoS attacks

7ï¸âƒ£ Do small Rails apps need CDN?

Not always.

You usually add CDN when:

App is public-facing

Users are global

Traffic is high

Pages are mostly read-only

